#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: ujjāyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Ujjayasutta"
msgstr "39. With Ujjaya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: ujjayo → ujjāyo (bj)
msgctxt "an4.39:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ujjayo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā "
"saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Ujjaya the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with "
"him."

msgctxt "an4.39:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho ujjayo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an4.39:1.3"
msgid "“bhavampi no gotamo yaññaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti?"
msgstr "“Does Master Gotama praise sacrifice?”"

msgctxt "an4.39:1.4"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi;"
msgstr "“Brahmin, I don’t praise all sacrifices."

msgctxt "an4.39:1.5"
msgid "na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi."
msgstr "Nor do I criticize all sacrifices."

msgctxt "an4.39:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpe kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe gāvo haññanti, ajeḷakā haññanti, "
"kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"Take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, "
"and various kinds of creatures are slaughtered."

msgctxt "an4.39:1.7"
msgid "evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi."
msgstr "I criticize that kind of violent sacrifice."

msgctxt "an4.39:1.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an4.39:1.9"
msgid ""
"Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā "
"arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannā."
msgstr ""
"Because neither perfected ones nor those who have entered the path to "
"perfection will attend such a violent sacrifice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.39:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpe ca kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, "
"na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and "
"pigs, and various kinds of creatures are not slaughtered."

msgctxt "an4.39:2.2"
msgid ""
"evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi, yadidaṃ niccadānaṃ "
"anukulayaññaṃ."
msgstr ""
"I praise that kind of non-violent sacrifice; for example, a regular gift as "
"an ongoing family sacrifice."

msgctxt "an4.39:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an4.39:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā "
"arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannāti."
msgstr ""
"Because perfected ones and those who have entered the path to perfection "
"will attend such a non-violent sacrifice."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.39:3.1"
msgid "Assamedhaṃ purisamedhaṃ,"
msgstr "Horse sacrifice, human sacrifice,"

# It’s curiously difficult to find meaningful info on these. The sammapasa seems to mean (following MW) the “casting” “prasa” of a “stick” “samya” as part of a ritual. Perhaps “javelin throwing?” Vajapeya is a high royal rite of autumn, see http://advaita-l.advaita-vedanta.narkive.com/AmaMNXZP/vajapeya-fwd. I can’t find any reference to niraggala. I don’t agree with the defn. in the PPN. Perhaps it refers to a sacrifice performed outdoors, or even something like a bullfight: relase the animals before killing them.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:3.2"
msgid "Sammāpāsaṃ vājapeyyaṃ niraggaḷaṃ;"
msgstr "the sacrifices of the ‘stick-casting’,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Mahāyaññā mahārambhā → sammāpāsaṃ vācapeyyaṃ; niraggalaṃ mahārambhā (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.39:3.3"
msgid "Mahāyaññā mahārambhā,"
msgstr "the ‘royal soma drinking’, and the ‘unbarred’—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:3.4"
msgid "Na te honti mahapphalā."
msgstr "these huge violent sacrifices yield no great fruit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.39:4.1"
msgid "Ajeḷakā ca gāvo ca,"
msgstr "The great sages of good conduct"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:4.2"
msgid "vividhā yattha haññare;"
msgstr "don’t attend sacrifices"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:4.3"
msgid "Na taṃ sammaggatā yaññaṃ,"
msgstr "where goats, sheep, and cattle,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:4.4"
msgid "upayanti mahesino."
msgstr "and various creatures are killed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.39:5.1"
msgid "Ye ca yaññā nirārambhā,"
msgstr "But the great sages of good conduct"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:5.2"
msgid "yajanti anukulaṃ sadā;"
msgstr "do attend non-violent sacrifices"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:5.3"
msgid "Ajeḷakā ca gāvo ca,"
msgstr "of regular family tradition,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vividhā nettha haññare → vividhā yattha haññare (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.39:5.4"
msgid "vividhā nettha haññare;"
msgstr "where goats, sheep, and cattle,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:5.5"
msgid "Tañca sammaggatā yaññaṃ,"
msgstr "and various creatures aren’t killed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:5.6"
msgid "upayanti mahesino."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: Etaṃ → evaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.39:6.1"
msgid "Etaṃ yajetha medhāvī,"
msgstr "An intelligent person should sacrifice like this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:6.2"
msgid "eso yañño mahapphalo;"
msgstr "for this sacrifice is very fruitful."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Etaṃ → evaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an4.39:6.3"
msgid "Etaṃ hi yajamānassa,"
msgstr "For a sponsor of sacrifices like this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:6.4"
msgid "seyyo hoti na pāpiyo;"
msgstr "things get better, not worse."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:6.5"
msgid "Yañño ca vipulo hoti,"
msgstr "Such a sacrifice is truly abundant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.39:6.6"
msgid "pasīdanti ca devatā”ti."
msgstr "and even the deities are pleased.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.39:6.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
